dc_description_s: AMS 1. North Decimal Degree 22.633333. South Decimal Degree 22.566667. East Decimal Degree 120.366667. West Decimal Degree 120.316667. Alternate title: Hozan. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals. Place names are transcribed according to the modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to Feng-shan [Fengshan]. Compiled in 1944 from aerial photgraphy dated from December 1943 to June 1944 by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2114-I, 1944; Formosa 1:25,000, Sheets 2114-I NW, 2114-I SW, 1944. Additional information from intelligence data.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
